#X text 267 121 Two 1st order allpass in series, f 9;
#X text 197 406 500hz: 6th order (Q = 0.5);
#X text 517 362 We also have a 6th order example. Note that unlike a comb filter \, we do not produce notches in a harmonic series (unless you get to tweak the Q for each frequency value \, which would be silly) - but that's the point of using allpass filters to create notches for something like a phaser as we'll see., f 66;
